name: My Waroeng
address: Jl. Raya Buitan, Manggis, Kec. Manggis, Kabupaten Karangasem, Bali, Indonesia
review 1:
This special place really saved our lives while we were visiting the area near Candidasa. The place is small but the perfect place to get a nice home cooked meal whether you are looking for Indonesian Food or some western food.

We stumbled upon this place one rainy night and knew we had to come back. They have dishes like Nasi Goreng as well as Ayam Sambal Matah and even pizzas and pastas as well.

Prices are super affordable with the maximum dish only costing 30K. Everything else in the area in terms of restaurants and warnings are more expensive than that.

We ordered the food to dine in and it is also good as take away. We also order the Ayam Sambal Matah and recently ordered the Bihun Goreng and cumi crispy which were all just super yum. The cumi squid was definitely a frozen packer but it didn‚Äôt bother me.

We love supporting local business and this one is truly a gem. At night they have a huge sign that has bright lights so you will never miss it!

Highly recommend when you are traveling to East Bali and craving a nice bite and meal that is home cooked.
review 2: The food here was so good we came back! It is also very cheap, we spent less than 80 for two meals with a good amount of food. The mie goreng was the best I‚Äôve had in Indonesia!
review 3: The food is amazing here. A great little place to grab some local food and the owner and family were very nice. Great price for quality Balinese food!
review 4: Friendly owner, yummy food also cheap price . If u want a traditional n spice food this the place üòã ,tasty ayam gebrek.
review 5: Really good service, great food quality and cheap price :)

name: Golden Lotus Corner
address: GG2R+597, Jl. Raya Buitan, Manggis, Kec. Manggis, Kabupaten Karangasem, Bali 80817, Indonesia
review 1:
The lady owner was delightful and spoke good English.

Gado-gado was absolutely amazing, the home made peanut sauce probably the best I've had in Bali.

name: Sjana Grill House
address: GG2V+85P, Jl. Raya Buitan, Sengkidu, Kec. Manggis, Kabupaten Karangasem, Bali 80871, Indonesia
review 1:
This nice cafe/restaurant is in the middle of nowhere, but it's very modern. It has both indoors and outdoor tables with delicious food that doesn't break the your wallet. The staff is friendly and accomodating. I would recommend this to tourists seeking cultural experience in Bali, it's along the way East if you're going to explore the island.

The place in general is very clean and also visually appealing as well.

They  have free wifi, which I'm currently using because for some reason my t-mobile plan (with international coverage) isn't giving me any service.
review 2:
We went there last night with Brad and Sandra from Bayshore.
Food was tasty.
Drinks cold and refreshing.
Great prices.
Staff friendly.
Very clean and tidy.
Deserve to get ahead. Well done to the family who own and run it.
Thanks Brad for taking us. Will do it again.
Pete and Chrissie Johnson.
review 3: Nice resraurant with good prices, i love the spaghetti carbonara and their balinese pizza. And for their "ice cream goreng" is so prety well. The waitress are friendly enaugh.
review 4: Nice foods and the price is cheap. The staff is friendly too.  I walk from my hotel (Karma royal candisa), took me 10mins. I will come again if i stay around Candidasa
review 5:
Such a wonderful little place to stop for a coffee en route to Amed. Very lovely staff.

Great prices. Great food and coffee.
